<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,150,429]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,223,249]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Monzen, K." box="[321,494,222,249]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="24 - 38" refId="ref48573" refString="Monzen, K. (1954) Revision of the Japanese gall wasps with the descriptions of new genus, subgenus, species and subspecies (II). Cynipidae (Cynipinae) Hymenoptera. Annual Reports of Gakugei Faculty of Iwate University, 6, 24 - 38." type="journal article" year="1954">Monzen (1954)</bibRefCitation>
identified the host plant of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1904" box="[797,953,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Neuroterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hakonensis">
<emphasis box="[797,953,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">N. hakonensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName box="[989,1142,223,249]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acutissima">
<emphasis box="[989,1142,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Q. acutissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[1214,1286,223,249]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Cerris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1214,1286,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Cerris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) while 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinji, O." pageId="28" pageNumber="29" refId="ref52964" refString="Shinji, O. (1944) Galls and gall insects. Shunyo-do, Tokyo, 580 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1944">Shinji (1944)</bibRefCitation>
identified the host plant as 
<taxonomicName box="[542,659,259,285]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serrata">
<emphasis box="[542,659,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Q. serrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[735,829,259,285]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[735,829,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Based on very strong oak section conservatism in a single generation of almost all 
<taxonomicName authority="(Stone et al. 2009)" baseAuthorityName="Stone" baseAuthorityYear="2009" box="[500,819,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cynipini">
Cynipini (
<bibRefCitation author="Stone, G. N. &amp; Hernandez-Lopez, A. &amp; Nicholls, J. A. &amp; di Pierro, E. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Melika, G. &amp; Cook, J. M." box="[614,811,295,321]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="854 - 869" refId="ref53165" refString="Stone, G. N., Hernandez-Lopez, A., Nicholls, J. A., di Pierro, E., Pujade-Villar, J., Melika, G. &amp; Cook, J. M. (2009) Extreme host plant conservatism during at least 20 million years of host plant pursuit by oak gallwasps. Evolution, 63, 854 - 869. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1558 - 5646.2008.00604. x" type="journal article" year="2009">
Stone 
<emphasis box="[687,743,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, both are unlikely to be true, and we regard the host(s) of this species as in need of confirmation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,150,429]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,366,392]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Biology.</emphasis>
Only the asexual generation has been described, which induces detachable leaf galls on an undetermined 
<taxonomicName box="[228,322,403,429]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[228,322,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see Remarks above) (Table 1; 
<bibRefCitation author="Monzen, K." box="[678,836,402,429]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="24 - 38" refId="ref48573" refString="Monzen, K. (1954) Revision of the Japanese gall wasps with the descriptions of new genus, subgenus, species and subspecies (II). Cynipidae (Cynipinae) Hymenoptera. Annual Reports of Gakugei Faculty of Iwate University, 6, 24 - 38." type="journal article" year="1954">Monzen 1954</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
